When #E(Fp) = p (or E.order() = p in Sagemath), which is Anomalous Elliptic Curve, we can use Smart's Attack to solve ECDLP

Resources: 
https://wstein.org/edu/2010/414/projects/novotney.pdf
https://crypto.stackexchange.com/questions/70454/why-smarts-attack-doesnt-work-on-this-ecdlp

Code: https://github.com/jvdsn/crypto-attacks/blob/master/attacks/ecc/smart_attack.py
